  "text.occult_codex.node.magic.tooltip": "§5The foundation of becoming a wizard",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion": "Magic Potions",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion.tooltip": "§5Learn them, experience the ancient alchemists",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1": "Elements",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.content": "Magic potionology is an ancient discipline that combines mysticism, herbalism, and alchemy, aiming to create potions with supernatural effects by blending natural substances imbued with magical energy. Its origins can be traced back to primitive shamanistic rituals, with lost civilizations and early alchemists significantly influencing its development. The core of potionology lies in understanding the spirituality of all things—from moon-soaked mandrakes to common grasses, each material carries unique elemental powers that must be activated through specific incantations, astrological timing, or ritual means.",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.content.title": "Elements",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.content_1": "Potion Elements",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.content_1.concentration": "Concentration Range: \n%s - %s",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.content_1.max_level": "Max Level: %s",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.content_1.max_time": "Max Time: %s",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.content_1.name": "Potion Element: %s",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.content_1.temperature_range": "Temperature Tolerance Range: \n%s - %s",
  "text.occult_codex.node.potion_1.tooltip": "§5The fundamental components of magic potions",
  "text.occult_codex.node.prologue": "Prologue",
  "text.occult_codex.node.prologue.tooltip": "§2The beginning of the story...",
  "text.occult_codex.node.prologue_1": "Development Team",
  "text.occult_codex.node.prologue_1.tooltip": "§6Join us! QQ Group: ",
  "text.occult_codex.node.prologue_2": "Background Story",
  "text.occult_codex.node.prologue_2.content": "My ears are still ringing as I lie on the ground, spitting up half a mouthful of sour water. The security alert sound from the subway gate seems to still echo, but now before my eyes are towering ferns that block out the sky. Two moons hang in the gaps between tree canopies, indigo and amber moonlight tearing strange patterns on the bark.\n\nThe thick book with copper-cornered binding presses against my ribs, its cover bearing faded gold lettering that reads 'Occult Codex'. As I try to open the title page, a crack suddenly runs across the spine—it's clearly an opening mouth.",
  "text.occult_codex.node.prologue_2.content.title": "Traveler from Another World",
  "text.occult_codex.node.prologue_2.tooltip": "§5Touch this text, listen to the whispers in the wind...",
